License terms for setec-voiceprint
==================================

This project ships under a dual license:

  Code (everything under scripts/) ......... [SOFTWARE LICENSE TBD]
  Documentation (README, ROADMAP, references/, SKILL.md, baselines/README.md,
                 CHANGELOG, this LICENSE notice) ........ [DOCUMENTATION LICENSE TBD]

The maintainer is finalizing the license choice. Recommended candidates:

  Code:
    - MIT (permissive, maximum reusability)
    - GNU GPL v3 (copyleft, share-alike for derivative software)

  Documentation:
    - CC BY-SA 4.0 (Creative Commons share-alike, the equivalent of GPL
      for prose; canonical for citation-friendly research artifacts)
    - CC BY 4.0 (permissive attribution-only equivalent)

The project's prose artifacts (the four files in references/, SKILL.md, the
README, the ROADMAP) are substantive editorial work and benefit from a license
designed for creative works. The Python tooling is software and benefits from
a license designed for software (CC licenses are not designed for code; the
Creative Commons FAQ explicitly recommends against using CC licenses for
software).

Once the licenses are chosen, this file will be replaced with the canonical
text of the chosen license(s) and any additional notices required by them.

Until then, use of this repository is governed by the maintainer's intent to
ship under one of the above pairings. Personal baseline corpora and voice
profiles are not part of this repository and are not licensed for
redistribution from any baseline structure shipped here.
